metadata.title: Me at the zoo
metadata.description: The first video on YouTube. Maybe it's time to go back to the zoo?

transcript.text: All right, so here we are in front of the elephants,
and the cool thing about these guys is that they have really, really, really long trunks.
And that's pretty much all there is to say.

summary:
1. The video is recorded at a zoo in front of elephant exhibits
2. The narrator highlights elephants' distinctive long trunks as their most notable feature
3. This is a brief, casual observation video with minimal commentary
4. The tone is informal and conversational
5. It represents one of YouTube's earliest uploaded videos
translation: 좋아요, 여기 코끼리 앞에 있습니다. 이 녀석들의 멋진 점은 정말, 정말, 정말 긴 코를 가지고 있다는 것입니다. 그리고 그것은 멋집니다. 그리고 그게 할 말의 전부입니다.
